==Russian==

===Verb===
'''шить''' (šit’) ''[[impf.]]'', [[сшить]] (sšit’) ''[[pf.]]''

#to [[sew]] ''(transitive)''
#:шить [[на]] [[машинка|маши́нке]] — ''to sew on a machine''
#to be occupied with sewing, to [[tailor]] ''(intransitive)'' ''(only impf.)''
#:Чем она занимается? Она шьёт. — ''What is she? She’s a dressmaker.''
#''(colloquial)'' to [[order]] (e.g., a dress)
#:хочу сшить себе костюм у Левинсона — ''I want to order a suit from Levinson’s''
#to [[embroider]] ''(only impf.)''
#:шить [[золото|зо́лотом]] — ''embroider [[in]] [[gold]]''
#:шито [[белый|бе́лыми]] [[нитка|ни́тками]] ''(saying)'' — ''(literally) embroidered in white thread'' (meaning transparent to anyone)
#:шить [[дело|де́ло]] {{colloquial}} — ''to cook up [[charges]]'' (''literally'': ''to embroider the case'')
#:(он) [[не]] [[лыко|лы́ком]] шит ''(saying)'' — ''(he) was not born yesterday'' (''literally'': ''(he) was not embroidered in [[bast]]'')
#:
#{{figurative}} to [[nail]] [[planking]]
#:шить [[плот]] — ''to make a [[raft]]''

